In Android phone Security settings, allow installation of apps from unknown sources.
Install each application package directly on phones running Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean) or above.

RECOMMENDATION: Verify each Android application package.

Do so by opening a terminal application and typing, for example:
$ unzip -p focus_groups.apk META-INF/CERT.RSA | keytool -printcert | grep SHA1

Check the fingerprint:
25:36:90:C2:D7:B8:99:CF:33:F8:B5:0A:D7:99:57:C6:EA:48:44:4D